mogriolling (noun, verb)

A bait-and-switch meme pattern derived from rickrolling, where the expected redirect to Rick Astley’s “Never Gonna Give You Up” is replaced with a compact informational payload (“mogri”).

Structure:
- bait: misleading or curiosity-inducing surface (e.g. encoded data, retro code, irrelevant label)
- trigger: execution or decoding step required to reveal content
- switch: substitution of expected media reveal with semantic payload
- payload: minimal statement preserving framework-level intent across contexts

Effect:
Maintains the recognisable rickroll format while inverting outcome from humorous misdirection to useful information delivery.

Usage:
- to mogrioll: deploy a bait-and-switch resolving to a mogri
- a mogrioll: an instance of such deployment
